    <h2 id="build-local---bug-testing">Build Local - Bug Testing</h2>

    <p>Buidling your site locally is the best way to figure out why it‚Äôs not publishing correctly via GitHub.</p>

    <p>You must set up your gemfile specifically for each theme.</p>

    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://bundler.io/">Install bundler</a></li>
    </ul>

    <p>then prepare bundler for your project:</p>

    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> bundle update

 bundle install
</code></pre></div>    </div>

    <p>Build gives an error message if the build fails</p>

    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> bundle exec jekyll build
</code></pre></div>    </div>

    <p>Serve builds and ‚Äúserves‚Äù a local browsable copy</p>

    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> bundle exec jekyll serve
</code></pre></div>    </div>

    <p>Trace gives details on errors (but won‚Äôt always show your problem)</p>

    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> bundle exec jekyll build --trace
</code></pre></div>    </div>

    <p>Verbose‚Ä¶ you get the idea.</p>

    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> bundle exec jekyll build --verbose
</code></pre></div>    </div>

